Senate President Ahmad Lawan has constituted an adhoc committee on media and public affairs for the 9th Senate. The committee, headed by Sen. Adedayo Adeyeye (APC, Ekiti), is saddled with the responsibility of interfacing with the media pending the setting up of the standing committee. Other members of the adhoc committee are Aishatu Dahiru (APC, Adamawa), Uba Sani (APC, Kaduna), Abba Moro (PDP, Benue), Ifeanyi Ubah (YPP, Anambra) and Betty Apiafi (PDP, Rivers). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE JUST IN: Lawan raises adhoc panel on legislative agenda Breaking: Senate probes Sen Elisha Abbo over assault allegations N/Assembly proceeds on Christmas, New Year break Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin